  "texts": [
    "Chinese dialects can be roughly divided into seven categories based on tone value, loudness, the composition of initials and finals, and geographical locations, namely Northern Mandarin, Wu dialect, Gan dialect, Hunan dialect, Fujian dialect, Cantonese dialect, and Hakka dialect (Social Sciences 2012; Yuan 1960).",
    "However, the research progress of DSR in different regions is distinct, such as specific recognition approaches, speech corpus, and so on.",
    "The construction of a dialect corpus is the crucial basis for dialect recognition (Bolia et al. 2000), but at present most corpora are dominated by Mandarin, and there are relatively few specific dialect corpora.",
    "So this paper organizes the literature on Chinese DSR and summarizes the dialect corpora constructed in recent years.",
    "Starting from the dialect division, we analyze the basic composition of the dialect corpus concretely."
  ],
